In response.py, line 274 (TestResponse.goto), self.charset can be None, which causes encode() to throw an exception. A patched snippet is below:

    # encode unicode strings for the outside world
    if not PY3 and getattr(self, '_use_unicode', False):
        def to_str(s):
            if isinstance(s, text_type):
                if self.charset is None:
                    self.charset = 'utf-8'
                return s.encode(self.charset)
            return s

